# Gospel Central frontend — environment contract.
# Copy to `.env.local` for local dev, or set these in the Vercel project env
# (per-environment rows: Production / Preview / Development).
#
# The app ships with an in-page MSW mock (src/mocks/) that fully drives the UI.
# That mock is PERMANENT dev/test/demo infrastructure — the real-backend cutover
# does NOT remove it; it just stops it intercepting. Two modes, selected ONLY by
# NEXT_PUBLIC_MOCK_API (a build-time NEXT_PUBLIC_ var — a change needs a redeploy):

# --- Mock mode (default) ---------------------------------------------------
# MSW patches window.fetch/XHR in-page (SW-free) and resolves same-origin /api.
NEXT_PUBLIC_MOCK_API=true

# --- Supabase mode (the real backend — solo build, project imjsdsepmhgazracegog)
# Flip MOCK_API to false AND set the two Supabase vars below; the app's api layer
# then routes through src/lib/api/supabase.ts (RLS-enforced) instead of the mock.
# The anon key is browser-safe (RLS still gates every row). NEVER put the
# service_role / sb_secret key in a NEXT_PUBLIC_ var. Rollback = flip MOCK_API
# back to true and redeploy.
# NOTE: the legacy NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL / localhost:8080 Go-backend path is retired.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_MOCK_API=false
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://imjsdsepmhgazracegog.supabase.co
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=<anon key from Supabase dashboard / reference memory>
